.TH QDSOUNDINGINDEX 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-qdtools" "SmartMet Tools"
.SH NAME
qdsoundingindex \- compute sounding-derived stability indices
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B qdsoundingindex
.RI [ options ]
.I qdin qdout
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B qdsoundingindex
reads sounding querydata and writes a new querydata file containing
derived stability and convective indices, including LCL, LFC and EL
levels and heights, and CAPE / CIN computed from the surface parcel,
the 500\ m mixed-layer parcel, and the most unstable parcel.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-n " name"
Producer name (defaults to the producer of the input).
.TP
.BI \-t " count"
Number of worker threads to use (default: all available cores).
.SH EXAMPLES
Compute stability indices for a sounding file:
.PP
.RS 4
qdsoundingindex sounding.sqd indices.sqd
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR qdsounding (1),
.BR temp2qd (1),
.BR qdinfo (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
